tinental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry de Lockwood was born about 1378, in Lockwood, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Lockwood, was 55 and his mother, Margaret De Dulverton, was 26. He married Lady Agnes De La Schaw about 1398, in York, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1378–":"umbes 1378–Surnud","1374–Male":"1374–Surnud","1378–Male":"1378–Surnud","1375–1486":"1375–1486","1404–1434":"1404–1434","1417–1448":"1417–1448","1325–Male":"1325–Surnud","1353–Female":"1353–Surnud","1404":"1404","1448":"1448","1325":"1325","1434":"1434","1378":"1378","ABT 1398":"umbes 1398","1486":"1486","1353":"1353","1375":"1375","1374":"1374","Abt 1378":"umbes 1378","1417":"1417","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lockwood, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lockwood, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lockwood, Yorkshire, England":"Lockwood, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1378–":"noin 1378–Kuollut","1374–Male":"1374–Kuollut","1378–Male":"1378–Kuollut","1375–1486":"1375–1486","1404–1434":"1404–1434","1417–1448":"1417–1448","1325–Male":"1325–Kuollut","1353–Female":"1353–Kuollut","1404":"1404","1448":"1448","1325":"1325","1434":"1434","1378":"1378","ABT 1398":"noin 1398","1486":"1486","1353":"1353","1375":"1375","1374":"1374","Abt 1378":"noin 1378","1417":"1417","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt 